{
  "stem": "6900.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he did this.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I was working, and he phoned me up one day, and he said, Sis-- he used to call me Sis-- Sis, he says, I've got news for you from the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want you to come to the office.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So I said, well, I can't leave, because, all these work people and girls I had under me, I can't leave till 5:00.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Doesn't matter, I'll wait for you.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which he did.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went to his office, and he gave me the Red Cross letter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it said that my daughter was buried-- died in Belsen and that my husband was in a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That my daughter-- God rest her soul-- died after the liberation, and that my husband was-- I don't know if this is true-- but there were five of the workers left, and they got shot.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That was that.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So then I thought, my daughter's buried in Belsen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Maybe-- I didn't know it was a mass grave, you see-- maybe I could get her body transferred to England and have her buried where my parents are buried, in a Jewish cemetery.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Because I've got the pictures of them in a Jewish cemetery.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he wrote again, and they said she was buried in a mass grave, which isn't true.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my husband was shot, so probably also.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- so I couldn't do anything about that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But Maurice has found out that, as she died after the liberation, she's buried in a grave with only those children that died there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he's going to do something about that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I want him to do something about that, which I know my son-- God bless him-- will do.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maurice?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I didn't find Maurice till I got to England.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
